               <desc type="building-data" xml:lang="en">
                  <p source="#bibl000064b-1" xml:lang="en">Dajue liushi Hall (大覺六師殿), now destroyed, was the second major <term>timber-frame</term> structure on the central axis of <placeName>Longxing Monastery</placeName>. Originally built during the <term ref="/keyword/k000055">Northern Song dynasty</term>'s Yuanfeng reign period (1078-1085 CE), it suffered extensive damage in the early 20th century and was beyond repair by the time Liang Sicheng had visited in 1933.</p>
                  <p source="#bibl000064b-1" xml:lang="en">Research suggests that the hall was nine bays wide and six bays deep, with a width of 53 meters and a depth of 35 meters, which made it the largest building in the complex. With a single-eaves hip-gable roof (xieshan <term ref="/keyword/k000143">歇山</term>（or shaliangtou <term ref="/keyword/k000185">厦兩頭</term>), the hall was dedicated to the historical Buddha, Sakyamuni, and the six Buddhas that predated him: Vipasyin, Sikhin, Visvabhu, Krakucchanda, Kanakamuni, and Kasyapa.</p>
                  <p source="#bibl000064b-1" xml:lang="zh-Hant">大覺六師殿為<placeName>隆興寺</placeName>中軸線上第二座主要木構建築。此殿始建於<term ref="/keyword/k000074">北宋</term>元豐年間（1078-1085）。但在1933年，梁思成探訪此址時已毀壞坍塌。</p> 
                  <p source="#bibl000064b-1" xml:lang="zh-Hant">大覺六師殿為<term>單檐</term><term ref="/keyword/k000143">歇山</term>（或<term ref="/keyword/k000185">厦兩頭）</term>頂建築，面闊九間，寬53米，進深六間，深35米，曾為隆興寺建築群中面積最大的建築。其中供奉釋迦摩尼佛以及釋迦摩尼佛以前的六佛像，即毗婆師佛、屍棄佛、毗舍浮佛、拘留孫佛、拘那舍牟尼佛、迦葉佛像。</p>
